  <div class="myPage">
    <div class="myPage-main">
      <div style="height: 100px;position:relative;"></div>
      <div class="myPage-main-content">
        <!---大标题--->
        <div class="myPage-headline">
          <h1 class="myPage-headline-content">
            <span style="color: #8768cd">.</span>
            <span style="color: #483b53;font-family: Aaargh;">Safety</span>
            <span style="color: #8768cd">.</span>
          </h1>
        </div>

        <!---文字段落--->
        <div class="myPage-paragraph" id="section1">
          <h2 class="myPage-paragraph-headline-h2">Safe Project Design</h2>
          <!-- 记住这里的h2就是标题 -->
          <p class="myPage-paragraph-content">
            <b>Great importance is attached to safety in our project design. </b>
          </p>
          <p class="myPage-paragraph-content">
            Firstly, we use <i>E. coli</i> as our chassis organisms, which poses no harm to individuals or environment.
            <i>E. coli</i>
            DH5α, DH10β, BL21(DE3) and BW25113 are utilized when we implement the experiments of molecular cloning,
            expression and verification.
          </p>
          <p class="myPage-paragraph-content">
            This year our team fight for deinking of waste paper and harmless treatment of wastewater. In the deinking
            part, we select a highly efficient deinking enzyme to promote the ink separation on the surface of waste
            paper.
            To bypass the expensive protein purification step of enzymes, we introduce the signal peptides into our
            project to secrete target proteins into the supernatant, then use the supernatant to treat waste paper.
            After deinking process, the paper will be treated with high temperature, which ensures that the engineering
            bacteria could not leak. In the wastewater treatment part, we selected MT2A and MT3 human metallothioneins
            and expressed them in engineered bacteria for adsorption of heavy metal ions in wastewater. To avoid the
            possibility of bacterial diffusion in the environment, we designed a blue-light-activated kill switch that
            will be activated when the bacteria are exposed to blue light then will trigger the death of the bacteria.
            Hence, by treating the effluent with blue light, we can ensure complete elimination of bacteria.
          </p>
          <p class="myPage-paragraph-content">
            All the proteins are totally harmless to human body. All the plasmids are harmless for human beings and none
            of our parts would raise any safety issue according to the current expertise.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!---插图演示--->
        <div class="myPage-paragraph" id="section2">
          <h2 class="myPage-paragraph-headline-h2">Safe Lab Work</h2>
          <p class="myPage-paragraph-content">
            The laboratory is equipped with the location of emergency exits, emergency ventilation devices,
            fire-fighting equipment, first aid kits, and so on. Every year after recruiting new members, we spend
            several weeks training them in basic laboratory operations and handling safety accidents. When entering the
            laboratory, we must wear laboratory clothes, gloves, and goggles. All bacterial culture mediums have
            undergone sterilization treatment. We strictly follow the BSL-1 regulations to dispose of all biological
            materials and metabolic waste. The laboratory is also equipped with specialized operators for handling
            hazardous materials and biological products.
          </p>
          <div class="myPage-paragraph-fig">
            <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4907/wiki/safety/safety-fig1.jpg" alt="">
            <div class="myPage-paragraph-fig-description"><b>Figure 1 First aid kits of our lab.</b>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="myPage-paragraph-content">
            At the same time, we invited laboratory safety engineer, Lina Wu, to conduct safety education for all team
            members when they officially got into the experimental phase.
          </p>
          <div class="myPage-paragraph-fig">
            <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4907/wiki/safety/safety-fig2.png" alt="">
            <div class="myPage-paragraph-fig-description"><b>Figure 2 Members learnt laboratory safety intentions.</b>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>


      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

